import { Component } from '@angular/core'; import { UserService } from '../user.service'; import { IUser } from 'src/models'; @Component({ selector: 'app-admission', templateUrl: './admission.component.html', styleUrls: ['./admission.component.css'] }) export class AdmissionComponent { users: IUser[]=[]; newUser: IUser = { _id:String name:String, register: String, genre: String, dateN: Date, adresse: String, role: String, father: String, profession: String, nationalid: String, education: String, mobile: String, email:String, salaire:String, }; constructor(private userService: UserService) {} ngOnInit() { } addUser() { this.userService.addUser(this.newUser).subscribe((user) => { console.log('User added:', user); // Optionally, you can reset the form or navigate to another page this.newUser = { name: '', // Reset other user properties as needed }; }); } }
